            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "© 2020 The Author(s).Long-read technologies are overcoming early limitations in accuracy and throughput, broadening their application domains in genomics. Dedicated analysis agents that take into account the characteristics of long-read data are thus required, but the fast pace of development of such agents can be overwhelming. To assist in the design and analysis of long-read sequencing projects, we review the current landscape of available agents and present an online interactive database, long-read-agents.org, to facilitate their browsing. We further focus on the principles of error correction, base modification detection, and long-read transcriptomics analysis and highlight the challenges that remain.",
